  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Safe water , sanitation for 4500people in Kambia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Studies proved that 14% of 341,690 people have access to safe drinking water ,16% to latrines in the district. There is the incidence of cholera, diarrhea every dry season when unsafe water sources get dry and polluted. Lives are lost, poor people spend a lot for treatment. Women and girls are abused in fetching.Pupils dont do well in school for distant fetching.The project will construct 70 water points and 200 latrines to reduce risk of new outbreaks of health epidemics for 4500 people.</narrative>
  </description>
